</div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bde1665702790929.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bde1665702790929.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bde1665702790929\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      IDE Header\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the U-Bar and menu icon at the top of the Uniface IDE to find and open development objects, open editors for selected objects, and access utilities.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"bde1665702790929__context_w2007ab1b7b1_w2008ab1b7_w2009ab1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"bde1665702790929__fig_d5018e1_d5019e1_d5020e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>IDE Header</figcaption>\n<img alt='IDE Header\"' class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ideheader.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"bde1665702790929__li_d2021e1_d2022e1_d2023e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">U-Bar—displays the URL of the current development object and enables you to navigate to other objects.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"bde1665702790929__li_d2024e1_d2025e1_d2026e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span>—maintain DTDs, signatures, global objects, translation tables, modeled properties, and language setups.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"bde1665702790929__li_d2027e1_d2028e1_d2029e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\"><img alt=\"Main menu icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"bde1665702790929__image_txq_jmd_5cc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/menuicon.png?_LANG=enus\"/>—icon for the Main Menu, from which you can create new projects, import and\n               export development objects, and access other utilities. </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"example\" id=\"bde1665702790929__example_nhp_f4l_lcc\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">How to:</span><div class=\"p\">\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"bde1665702790929__ul_x2t_n4l_lcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bde1665702790929__li_d2030e1_d2031e1_d2032e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fii1695716579859.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fii1695716579859.html\" title=\"Use the Main U-Bar to locate and open development objects for editing. You can browse and search for objects by object type and name, or enter a complete object URL. As you enter text, the U-Bar offers suggestions that are appropriate to the current context.\">Find and Open Objects Using the Main U-Bar</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bde1665702790929__li_d2033e1_d2034e1_d2035e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"adn1665702696511.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/adn1665702696511.html\" title=\"It is only possible to import development objects that have been exported from a compatible Uniface Repository. Data is considered compatible if it comes from the same Repository version, or if it can be migrated to the current Repository.\">Import Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525983\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525983\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "IDE Header Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 IDE Header Use the U-Bar and menu icon at the top of the Uniface IDE to find and open development objects, open editors for selected objects, and access utilities. Figure 1. IDE Header U-Bar—displays the URL of the current development object and enables you to navigate to other objects. More Editors —maintain DTDs, signatures, global objects, translation tables, modeled properties, and language setups. —icon for the Main Menu, from which you can create new projects, import and export development objects, and access other utilities. How to: Find and Open Objects Using the Main U-Bar Import Development Objects Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}